* Not easy, convenient to use a ready built one.
* Entry point - what happens? what does the main function do? who controls it?
* Application layer - Deals with app lifecycle and events. Rendering frames, etc.
* Window layer - Inputs and events, propogating code.
* Renderer - What renders graphics.
* Render API abstraction - multiple, just OpenGL to start with.
* Debugging support - Scaffolding.
* Scripting - LUA/ C#.
* Memory - Allocation for it around performance.
* Entity-component system (ECS) - Game objects and modularise them.
* Physics solution.
* File I/O and Virtual File System.
* Build System - 3D model optimiser.
